@node "Example" "Included example"


 The file "3fis.seq" shows how to run predator on the  example  of  the  FIS
protein  and  related  proteins  found  in the @{fg shine}SWISSPROT@{fg text} database by a @{fg shine}FASTA
@{fg text}search.

1) predator -h 3fis.seq             @{" Run now " system "run >CON:0/20/640/150/Predator/CLOSE/WAIT Example/Run_Exmp_1 guide"}

 Sice -u option has not been specified, PREDATOR will find the  FIS  protein
in its  sequence/structure database and will simply use the known assignment
as prediction:

2) predator -h 3fis.seq -u          @{" Run now " system "run >CON:0/20/640/150/Predator/CLOSE/WAIT Example/Run_Exmp_2 guide"}

 A genuine prediction will be generated for the first sequence  in  the  set
(3fis) using other sequences:

3) predator -h 3fis.seq -s -u       @{" Run now " system "run >CON:0/20/640/150/Predator/CLOSE/WAIT Example/Run_Exmp_3 guide"}

 A genuine prediction will be generated for the first sequence  in  the  set
(3fis) without using other sequences (single sequence prediction).


 @{" Go to using options " link "Using" 0}
@endnode

