@node "Amiga_Introduction" "AmigaDOS Introduction"


 This package is only an AmigaDOS porting of the  program  called  @{b}PREDATOR@{ub},
which  is  able  to  predict  the protein secondary structure. A very simple
interface, based on reqtools.library, was added to Workbench use.
 This version of PREDATOR was developed on my my accelerated A1200  (030/881
50  MHz,  16 Mb Fast Ram, HD 1080 Mb, CD-ROM 4X, two external floppy drives)
with GNU C V 2.7.0, Amiga E V3.2a, Enforcer V37, GoldEd V3.1.3  and  Heddley
V1.1.


@{b}Requirements:@{ub}
 - AmigaDOS 2.04 or better.
 - CPU 68000 or better.
 - FPU not required but strongly raccomanded.
 - About 2 Mb of RAM (but this is in function of database dimensions used
   in the secondary structure prediction).
 - At least the release 41 of Ixemul.library (included the 68000 version).
 - At least the release 37 of reqtools.library (included).
 - About 1 Mb of free disk space (with sources).


@{b}File descriptions:@{ub}
 Predator.guide             This hypertext guide
 AmiPred                    Workbench interface for PREDATOR
 Install                    Install script
 Example/3fis.seq           Multisequence for tests
 Example/Run_Exmp_1         Script to automatic run the first example
 Example/Run_Exmp_2         Script to automatic run the second example
 Example/Run_Exmp_3         Script to automatic run the third example
 Exe/dssp.dat               Database for PREDATOR
 Exe/Predator_000           PREDATOR executable 68000 version
 Exe/Predator_020           PREDATOR executable 68020 version
 Exe/Predator_020881        PREDATOR executable 68020/68881 version
 Exe/Predator_040           PREDATOR executable 68040 version (not tested)
 Exe/stride.dat             Database for PREDATOR
 Src [DRAWER]               All sources and makefiles
@endnode

@node "Amiga_Installation" "Installation of AmigaDOS version"


 The installation procedure is very  easy,  why  is  operated  by  Commodore
Installer (not present in this package).  It's  possible  perform  a  manual
installation,  but remember to set the environment variable @{b}PRE_DIR@{ub} with the
directory who PREDATOR executable is installed. During manual  file  coping,
you must choose the correct PREDATOR version for your system:

 Predator_000       for 68000 and 68010 systems.
 Predator_020       for 68020 and 68030 systems without math coprocessor.
 Predator_020881    for 68020 and 68030 systems with 68881 or 68882.
 Predator_040       for 68040 and 68060 systems (?) (not tested).



                          @{" Install PREDATOR now ! " system "Installer Install APPNAME PREDATOR MINUSER AVERAGE DEFUSER EXPERT NOLOG"}
@endnode

