@node "Amiga_Usage" "Usage of AmigaDOS version"


 PREDATOR can be invoked in two ways: from shell  and  from  workbench.  The
shell invokation is totally identical as the @{" UNIX version " link "Using" 0}.

@{b}Workbench invokation.@{ub}
 You can launch PREDATOR directly from workbench "dobleclicking" on  AmiPred
icon.  This  program, written in E, allow to pass the parameters to PREDATOR
executable trough reqtool.library requesters.
 In a first time, you can specify the single or multisequence file and  then
the  output  file.  If this last parameter is not specified, AmiPred use the
console as output stream. At the end, you can  introduce  the  same  options
with the same sintax of the @{" UNIX version " link "Using" 0}.



                            @{" Run AmiPred now ! " system "Run AmiPred"}
@endnode

